<bibRefCitation author="Maldonado" box="[1230,1424,607,633]" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" refId="ref18070" refString="Maldonado C., J. (1990) Systematic catalogue of the Reduviidae of the World. Caribbean Journal of Science. Special publication No. 1. University of Puerto Rico, Mayaguez, 694 pp." type="book" year="1990">Maldonado 1990</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Wygodzinsky, P." box="[151,391,643,669]" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" pagination="1 - 102" refId="ref18604" refString="Wygodzinsky, P. (1949) Elenco sistematico de los reduviiformes americanos. Instituto de Medicina Regional de la Universidad Nacional de Tucuman, Monografia, 1, 1 - 102." type="journal article" year="1949">Wygodzinsky (1949)</bibRefCitation>
, however, stated that the type locality was probably erroneous; 
<bibRefCitation author="Carpintero, D. J." box="[1123,1326,643,669]" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" pagination="177 - 286" refId="ref16326" refString="Carpintero, D. J. (1978) Revision del genero Pothea Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843. Sus species en la Argentina (Hemiptera, Reduviidae, Ectrichodiinae). Revista del Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales Bernardino Rivadavia, 5, 177 - 286." type="journal article" year="1978">Carpintero (1978)</bibRefCitation>
endorsed this opinion. 
<bibRefCitation author="Froeschner, R. C." box="[299,506,679,705]" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" pagination="616 - 651" refId="ref17044" refString="Froeschner, R. C. (1988) Family Reduviidae Latreille, 1807 - The assassin bugs. In: Henry, T. J. &amp; Froeschner, R. C. (Eds.), Catalog of the Heteroptera, or true bugs, of Canada and the continental United States. E. J. Brill, New York, pp. 616 - 651. https: // doi. org / 10.1201 / 9781351070447 - 36" type="book chapter" year="1988">Froeschner (1988)</bibRefCitation>
claimed that all subsequent records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Maldonado" authorityYear="1990" box="[948,1106,680,705]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Pothea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneonitens">
<emphasis box="[948,1106,680,705]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">P. aeneonitens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from “America borealis” appear to be based on the original description, while several authors pointed out that the locality was probably wrong, and therefore he excluded the species from the fauna of America north of 
<collectingCountry box="[985,1074,751,777]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Fracker, S. B." box="[1085,1253,751,777]" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" pagination="217 - 252" refId="ref17011" refString="Fracker, S. B. (1912) A Systematic outline of the Reduviidae of North America. Proceedings of the Iowa Academy of Science, 19, 217 - 252." type="journal article" year="1912">Fracker (1912)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Maldonado" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" refId="ref18070" refString="Maldonado C., J. (1990) Systematic catalogue of the Reduviidae of the World. Caribbean Journal of Science. Special publication No. 1. University of Puerto Rico, Mayaguez, 694 pp." type="book" year="1990">Maldonado (1990)</bibRefCitation>
, however, listed the species specifically from “Southern states” and “S 
<collectingCountry box="[1042,1103,787,813]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">USA</collectingCountry>
”, respectively. Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Carpintero, D. J. &amp; Maldonado C." pageId="4" pageNumber="443" pagination="449 - 456" refId="ref16406" refString="Carpintero, D. J. &amp; Maldonado C., J. (1990) Contributions to the knowledge of American Ectrichodiinae. II. Notes about Rhiginia and Pothea (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Journal of agriculture of the University of Puerto Rico, 74, 449 - 456." type="journal article" year="1990">Carpintero &amp; Maldonado (1990)</bibRefCitation>
also insisted that the species was probably described in error from “America borealis”, in a subsequent paper they (
<bibRefCitation author="Carpintero, D. J. &amp; Maldonado C." box="[461,810,859,886]" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" pagination="125 - 141" refId="ref16459" refString="Carpintero, D. J. &amp; Maldonado C., J. (1996) Diagnostic characters and key to the genera of American Ectrichodiinae (Heteroptera, Reduviidae). Caribbean Journal of Science, 32, 125 - 141." type="journal article" year="1996">Carpintero &amp; Maldonado 1996</bibRefCitation>
) recorded that species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[1096,1175,859,885]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Pothea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1096,1175,859,885]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">Pothea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur from the 
<collectingCountry box="[1353,1407,859,885]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">USA</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[151,266,895,921]" name="Argentina" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dougherty, V." box="[277,478,894,921]" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" pagination="173 - 225" refId="ref16636" refString="Dougherty, V. (1995) A review of the New World Ectrichodiinae genera (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 121, 173 - 225." type="journal article" year="1995">Dougherty (1995)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Maldonado" authorityYear="1990" box="[590,748,896,921]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Pothea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneonitens">
<emphasis box="[590,748,896,921]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">P. aeneonitens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only from 
<collectingCountry box="[873,928,896,922]" name="Peru" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">Peru</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Costa, L. A. A." box="[939,1254,894,921]" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" pagination="400 - 404" refId="ref17520" refString="Gil-Santana, H. R. &amp; Costa, L. A. A. (2005) Pothea furtadoi sp. nov. (Hemiptera, Heteroptera, Reduviidae, Ectrichodiinae) de Mato Grosso e Minas Gerais, Brasil. Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 22, 400 - 404. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / s 0101 - 81752005000200014" type="journal article" year="2005">Gil-Santana &amp; Costa (2005)</bibRefCitation>
argued that taking into account that a label attached to the male 
<typeStatus box="[693,780,932,958]" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">syntype</typeStatus>
of this species reads “ 
<emphasis box="[1027,1141,931,957]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">Nordamer</emphasis>
. / Coll. Signoret.” (
<bibRefCitation author="Sehnal, C." pageId="4" pageNumber="443" refId="ref18233" refString="Sehnal, C. (2000) Typenkatalog der Reduviidae des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien (Insecta: Heteroptera). (Kataloge der wissenschaftlichen Sammlungen des Naturhistorisches Museum in Wien. Band 14. Entomologie. Heft 6. Naturhistorisches Museum, Vienna, 126 pp." type="book" year="2000">Sehnal 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[221,288,967,993]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1491,1516]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,234,1463]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,234,1463]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Pothea aeneonitens Stål, 1864. 1–2, male syntype deposited in NHM, 1, dorsal view; 2, labels; 3–6, male specimens from French Guiana; 3–4, dorsal view, scale bar 5.0 mm; 5, abdomen, ventral view, scale bar 2.0 mm; 6, head, lateral view, scale bar 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3856543" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3856543/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), if an error existed it was not of the author of the species (
<bibRefCitation author="Stal, C." box="[938,1049,966,994]" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" pagination="47 - 68" refId="ref18432" refString="Stal, C. (1864) Hemiptera nonnula nova vel minus cognita. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 4, 47 - 68. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.1863.11755428" type="journal article" year="1864">Stål 1864</bibRefCitation>
). In this case, a mislabeling should be hypothesized as the source of the supposed wrong information about the collecting origin of the specimen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,498,1390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">
There is only a single male deposited in NHM that formed part of the type material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Maldonado" authorityYear="1990" box="[1186,1345,1040,1065]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Pothea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneonitens">
<emphasis box="[1186,1345,1040,1065]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">P. aeneonitens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sehnal, C." pageId="4" pageNumber="443" refId="ref18233" refString="Sehnal, C. (2000) Typenkatalog der Reduviidae des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien (Insecta: Heteroptera). (Kataloge der wissenschaftlichen Sammlungen des Naturhistorisches Museum in Wien. Band 14. Entomologie. Heft 6. Naturhistorisches Museum, Vienna, 126 pp." type="book" year="2000">Sehnal 2000</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[220,324,1075,1101]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1491,1516]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,234,1463]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,234,1463]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Pothea aeneonitens Stål, 1864. 1–2, male syntype deposited in NHM, 1, dorsal view; 2, labels; 3–6, male specimens from French Guiana; 3–4, dorsal view, scale bar 5.0 mm; 5, abdomen, ventral view, scale bar 2.0 mm; 6, head, lateral view, scale bar 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3856543" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3856543/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
). As based on the original description of the species it is not possible to be sure if other type specimens exist, it is considered as a 
<typeStatus box="[510,601,1112,1138]" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">syntype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,498,1390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">
Two males from the 
<collectingCountry box="[434,601,1147,1173]" name="French Guiana" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
examined in course of present study (
<figureCitation box="[1033,1140,1147,1174]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1491,1516]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,234,1463]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,234,1463]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Pothea aeneonitens Stål, 1864. 1–2, male syntype deposited in NHM, 1, dorsal view; 2, labels; 3–6, male specimens from French Guiana; 3–4, dorsal view, scale bar 5.0 mm; 5, abdomen, ventral view, scale bar 2.0 mm; 6, head, lateral view, scale bar 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3856543" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3856543/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">Figs. 3–6</figureCitation>
) agree well with the short original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Stal, C." box="[388,499,1182,1210]" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" pagination="47 - 68" refId="ref18432" refString="Stal, C. (1864) Hemiptera nonnula nova vel minus cognita. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 4, 47 - 68. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.1863.11755428" type="journal article" year="1864">Stål 1864</bibRefCitation>
) of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Maldonado" authorityYear="1990" box="[548,707,1184,1209]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Pothea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneonitens">
<emphasis box="[548,707,1184,1209]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">P. aeneonitens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the male 
<typeStatus box="[872,959,1184,1210]" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">syntype</typeStatus>
deposited in NHM (
<figureCitation box="[1197,1264,1183,1209]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1491,1516]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,234,1463]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,234,1463]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Pothea aeneonitens Stål, 1864. 1–2, male syntype deposited in NHM, 1, dorsal view; 2, labels; 3–6, male specimens from French Guiana; 3–4, dorsal view, scale bar 5.0 mm; 5, abdomen, ventral view, scale bar 2.0 mm; 6, head, lateral view, scale bar 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3856543" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3856543/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="443">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); body lengths (measured to the tip of the hemelytra, which slightly surpasses the tip of the abdomen) of both non-types measured 
<quantity box="[151,253,1254,1282]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" unit="mm" value="13.5">13.5 mm</quantity>
, closely matching to the value provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stal, C." box="[741,867,1254,1282]" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" pagination="47 - 68" refId="ref18432" refString="Stal, C. (1864) Hemiptera nonnula nova vel minus cognita. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 4, 47 - 68. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.1863.11755428" type="journal article" year="1864">Stål (1864)</bibRefCitation>
(
<quantity box="[882,966,1255,1282]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="443" unit="mm" value="14.0">14 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
